      "db_column": "return_date",
      "amazon_header": "return-date",
      "type": "date",
      "note": "Sparsely populated by Amazon. Verified 2026-05-07 across 947 lifetime test rows: only 73 (7.7%) have a non-NULL value; recent rows uniformly NULL. Parser maps the column correctly — empty values mean Amazon shipped no return-date for that row. The column is part of UNIQUE_COLS but PostgreSQL allows multiple NULL rows under composite-key uniqueness, so dedup still works on (store_id, order_id, sku, fulfillment_center_id) when return_date is NULL. Treat as best-effort: when filtering on a date range, expect to miss most rows. Alternative: filter by `report_date` (always present)."
